title: Friendly Zoo Smoke Test
story: friendly-zoo
description: Baseline — story loads, rooms/items/readables/navigation/daemons render through the v2 phrase pipeline.

# This is the clean baseline established when Friendly Zoo was ported to the v2
# workspace (a port of the Family Zoo tutorial's final multi-file version). It
# asserts only on stable, correct output. Known v2 phrase-pipeline issue NOT
# asserted here: entities with already-plural names double-pluralize in the
# contents list ("pygmy goatses") — tracked separately as a platform finding.
---

# --- Zoo Entrance: opening room + contents list (phrase algebra) ---
> look
[OK: contains "Zoo Entrance"]
[OK: contains "Willowbrook"]

# Identity description through the phrase path
> examine yourself
[OK: contains "visitor"]

# Take an item — mutation + report
> take map
[OK: contains "Taken"]

# Readable through the phrase path (implicit take, then read)
> read brochure
[OK: contains "WILLOWBROOK FAMILY ZOO"]
[OK: contains "EXHIBITS"]

# --- Navigation: south to the Main Path ---
> south
[OK: contains "Main Path"]

# --- East to the Petting Zoo (animals + feed dispenser) ---
> east
[OK: contains "Petting Zoo"]
[OK: contains "feed dispenser"]
